<br>
It's not a positional issue, from my experience.  I have gotten this bug, casually walking up to someone who is afk (i.e. hasn't moved for a few minutes), standing still in front of them for a little while, then hitting perf.  And no, they were not ld.<br>
<br>
My theory on this is that it is a simple packet loss issue.  When you press the PA button several things happen.  First it sends a message to the server that you performed a PA.  The server takes that request, processes it, determines position, damage, etc. and sends you back a message.<br>
<br>
What also happens, is that *client side* when you press the PA button (or any style button), it automatically puts you into attack mode, regardless of what is happening server or link side.<br>
<br>
So what I see happening is that the request to PA is getting dropped or lost somehow, but the client (since there is no lag of course) still goes into attack mode.  So your client starts sending the fact you are in attack mode to the server, and you hit with a regular non styled hit.<br>
<br>
The big question is why this is happening so much more often now. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub175.ezboard.com/unandurius.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Nandurius</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(6/20/02 3:00:37 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3573.topic&index=31>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.ccs.neu.edu/home/phaas/phazer-avatar.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Ppl blocking/evading/parrying/me missing my PA?</span><hr size=1> <br>
